# Pigeon-eye Project Rules & Standards

## Tech Stack & Sponsor Alignment
- Frontend: Next.js 15 (App Router), Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI.
- Backend: Convex (Strict schema, use Actions for AI/Heavy logic).
- AI (Vision): Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite (Primary), Featherless AI (Backup for open-weight models).
- Automation: n8n (External webhooks for municipality escalation).
- Voice: ElevenLabs (Voice feedback for reports and accessibility).
- Observability: LangChain/LangSmith (Tracing for all LLM calls).

## Architecture Patterns
- Mobile-first PWA design.
- Internationalization: next-intl (German/English). Heilbronn-centric.
- Map: Leaflet (Default) for real-time issue tracking.
- Type Safety: Zod for AI JSON validation and Convex schema.

## Coding Style
- RAW and real: No boilerplate sugarcoating. Direct, efficient code.
- Functional components, Server Components by default.
- Convex hooks only: useQuery, useMutation, useAction.
- All UI text must be wrapped in translations (messages/de.json).

## Subagent Roles
- @Architect: Focuses on Convex schema and API bridges.
- @Visionary: Handles Gemini image analysis and Featherless integration.
- @Automator: Builds n8n webhooks and LangChain traces.
- @Voice: Manages ElevenLabs speech synthesis.

- Deployment: Vercel (Edge Runtime for AI routes where possible).
- Environment Variables: All keys (CONVEX_URL, GEMINI_API_KEY, ELEVENLABS_API_KEY) must be accessed via process.env with safety checks.
- Image Optimization: Use next/image for all UI elements.
- Build Safety: Strict TypeScript checks. No 'any' in Convex actions.
- PWA: Ensure manifest.json and service workers are Vercel-compatible (next-pwa).
